LEF (Lazyx's Executable Format), is a position independant executable format in
the following format:
A header of 32 bytes:
 offset | size | description
--------+------+-------------------------------------
    0   |  8   | Program's entry point
    8   |  8   | Size of text segment
    16  |  8   | Size of initialized data segment
    24  |  8   | Size of uninitialized data segment

The file itself with the code (text segment) and then the initialized data.
